<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FC73398FFB8C" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" box="[199,1163,1015,1042]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Body (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FEF7FC733C50FB8C" box="[275,340,1015,1041]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionTargetBox="[161,1436,533,1906]" captionTargetId="figure-159@2.[151,1436,525,1910]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Habitus 1 N. ingentis; 2 N. resimus; 3 N. leigongensis; 4 N. yujiei; 5 N. muricatus; 6 N. excertus; 7 N. serratus. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554672" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6554672/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
) dark brown; legs yellowish brown; antennae dark brown to light brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FB9F3828FBC4" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Head (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FEF5FB9F3C57FBA8" box="[273,339,1051,1077]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) 1.06–1.11 times as long as wide; punctation very dense, moderately coarse, distinctly umbilicate, interstices lacking microsculpture; postocular portion approximately 1.8–2.1 times as long as eye length.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FBE03EA5FB58" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FEA2FBE73C8EFBE0" box="[326,394,1123,1149]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) 1.12–1.18 times as long as wide, 0.95–1.02 times as long and 0.88–0.96 times as broad as head; punctation non-umbilicate, moderately dense and as coarse as that of head; midline posteriorly with short and very narrow impunctate elevation; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FB4B3885FA90" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Elytra (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FEFBFB4B3C61FB74" box="[287,357,1231,1257]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
) 0.63–0.72 times as long as wide, 0.53–0.61 times as long and 0.94–0.99 times as broad as pronotum; punctation as dense as, and slightly coarser than that of pronotum; interstices lacking microsculpture.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FA933932FAC8" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Abdomen with punctation dense and rather coarse on tergites III–V, dense and less coarse on tergite VI, moderately dense and fine on tergites VII–VIII; interstices lacking microsculpture.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FADB3893FA7B" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
Male. Sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FE42FADB3CEEFAE4" box="[422,490,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
) with posterior margin U-shaped emarginated in the middle. Sternite VIII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FAA5FADB3890FAE4" box="[1345,1428,1375,1401]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
) with U-shaped posterior excision. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FD7DFA073E1EFA00" box="[665,794,1411,1437]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Figs 11, 12</figureCitation>
) well sclerotized; with ventral process long and straight, widened near middle in ventral view; dorso-lateral apophyses moderately strong, distinctly curved in ventral view, curved dorsally and subtriangularly widened near apical third in lateral view, not reaching apex of ventral process.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF0FFC1FF23FA6B3C6AF920" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23FA6B3E6BF9B3" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF0FFC1FF23FA6B3F36F994" bold="true" box="[199,562,1519,1545]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Distribution and habitat data.</emphasis>
The species is known from Leigong Mt. in eastern 
<collectingRegion id="C120C9B8FFF0FFC1FB60FA6B39ECF994" box="[1156,1256,1519,1545]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
. The specimens were collected by sifting leaf litter at altitudes of 
<quantity id="C41CAABFFFF0FFC1FD5BF9973E6FF9B3" box="[703,875,1555,1582]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.15" metricValueMin="1.55" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" unit="m" value="1850.0" valueMax="2150.0" valueMin="1550.0">
<geoCoordinate id="66D0619DFFF0FFC1FD5BF9973FF9F9B3" box="[703,765,1555,1582]" degrees="1,550" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" precision="55" value="1.55">1,550</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate id="66D0619DFFF0FFC1FD18F9973E4FF9B3" box="[764,843,1555,1582]" degrees="2,150" direction="west" orientation="longitude" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" precision="55" value="-2.15">–2,150</geoCoordinate>
m
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23F9B33C6AF920" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF0FFC1FF23F9B33CABF9CC" bold="true" box="[199,431,1591,1617]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Comparative notes.</emphasis>
The new species is very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="C4E47CD9FFF0FFC1FCCEF9BC3985F9CC" authority="Watanabe &amp; Xiao" authorityName="Watanabe &amp; Xiao" box="[810,1153,1591,1617]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Nazeris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="giganteus">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF0FFC1FCCEF9BC3EB2F9CC" box="[810,950,1592,1617]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">N. giganteus</emphasis>
Watanabe &amp; Xiao
</taxonomicName>
, (
<bibRefCitation id="67757AABFFF0FFC1FB75F9B33DA2F9E8" author="Watanabe, Y. &amp; Xiao, N. N." pageId="1" pageNumber="42" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref6789" refString="Watanabe, Y. &amp; Xiao, N. N. (1997) Four new Nazeris (Coleoptera, Staphylinidae) from Yunnan Province, Southwest China. Edaphologia, 58, 1 - 12." type="journal article" year="1997">Watanabe &amp; Xiao 1997: 3</bibRefCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FF51F9DF3C51F9EB" box="[181,341,1627,1654]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 1–7" captionStart-1="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId-0="2.[151,264,1933,1957]" captionStartId-1="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox-0="[161,1436,533,1906]" captionTargetBox-1="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId-0="figure-159@2.[151,1436,525,1910]" captionTargetId-1="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId-0="2" captionTargetPageId-1="3" captionText-0="FIGURES 1–7. Habitus 1 N. ingentis; 2 N. resimus; 3 N. leigongensis; 4 N. yujiei; 5 N. muricatus; 6 N. excertus; 7 N. serratus. Scale bars: 1.0 mm." captionText-1="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6554672" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6554672/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Figs 1, 2, 6–8</figureCitation>
) in general appearance and aedeagal characters, but can be separated by the U-shaped posterior excision of male sternite VII (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FE11F9FB3F38F904" box="[501,572,1663,1689]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
), and by the smaller subtriangular expansion of dorso-lateral apophyses of aedeagus (
<figureCitation id="9BDF1BDFFFF0FFC1FEE9F9273C64F920" box="[269,352,1699,1725]" captionStart="FIGURES 8–12" captionStartId="3.[151,264,1459,1483]" captionTargetBox="[151,1426,192,1421]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[151,1436,181,1435]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURES 8–12. Nazeris ingentis 8 forebody; 9 male sternite VII; 10 male sternite VIII; 11 aedeagus in ventral view; 12 aedeagus in lateral view. Scale bars: 8 1.0 mm; 9–12 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6552147" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6552147/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4BFE54D1FFF0FFC1FF23F94339FEF97C" box="[199,1274,1735,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="035B075AFFF0FFC1FF23F94339FEF97C" blockId="1.[151,1437,835,1762]" box="[199,1274,1735,1762]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">
<emphasis id="3190DB48FFF0FFC1FF23F9433C4AF97C" bold="true" box="[199,334,1735,1761]" pageId="1" pageNumber="42">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet (Latin, adjective: large) alludes to the large size of this species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
